get.description:
### Description
Get payment request information for a payment previously created through the API.
The status information will be available during at least 30 calendar days after the creation of the Payment Request.
### Prerequisites

 * The TPP must be [registered][registration] as a PISP;
 * The TPP must access the API using a [Client Credentials][oauth2-endpoints] access token;
 * The TPP must have previously created the payment, using an access token associated with the same OAuth Client ID;
 * The TPP must send the request respecting the requirements for using the CIC [Open Banking API][open-banking-api];

  [registration]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/registration.html
  [oauth2-endpoints]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/oauth2-endpoints.html
  [open-banking-api]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/open-banking-api.html
  [sca-workflows]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/sca-workflows.html

post.description:
### Description

After a cancellation request `PUT /payment-requests/{paymentRequestResourceId}`,
the PISP must call this endpoint with the nonce to effect the payment
cancellation.

### Prerequisites

 * The TPP must be [registered][registration] as a PISP;
 * The TPP must access the API using a [Client Credentials][oauth2-endpoints] access token;
 * The TPP must have previously created the payment, using an access token associated with the same OAuth Client ID;
 * The PSU must have successfully completed the SCA process and confirmed the operation;
 * The TPP must have sent a cancellation request on `PUT /payment-requests/{paymentRequestId}` and obtained a nonce;
 * The TPP must send the request respecting the requirements for using the CIC [Open Banking API][open-banking-api];

### SCA Workflows and validation

No SCA is required for cancellation - the call to this endpoint is only
protected by the presence of the nonce returned by the previous `PUT`,
to link the confirmation HTTP request with the cancellation request.

  [registration]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/registration.html
  [oauth2-endpoints]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/oauth2-endpoints.html
  [open-banking-api]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/open-banking-api.html
  [sca-workflows]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/sca-workflows.html

### Description

After redirection, the TPP must call this endpoint with an authorization code
access token obtained during the [SCA process][sca-workflows] to confirm
payment initiation.

### Prerequisites

 * The TPP must be [registered][registration] as a PISP;
 * The TPP must have previously created the payment, using an access token associated with the same OAuth Client ID;
 * The PSU must have successfully completed the SCA process and confirmed the operation, transmitting an authorization code to the PISP;
 * The PISP must have successfully exchanged the authorization code with an access token, as in OAuth 2 Authorization Code flow;
 * The TPP must send the request respecting the requirements for using the CIC [Open Banking API][open-banking-api];
 * The TPP must access the API using the [Authorization Code][oauth2-endpoints] access token associated to the PSU's SCA;

### SCA Workflows and validation

The only SCA Workflow supported by this API is the REDIRECT workflow.
That workflow is described on the [SCA Workflows][sca-workflows] page
on the Developer Portal.

  [registration]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/registration.html
  [oauth2-endpoints]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/oauth2-endpoints.html
  [open-banking-api]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/open-banking-api.html
  [sca-workflows]: https://www.cic.fr/oauth2/en/devportal/sca-workflows.html

